<HEADLINE>
UCLA HURTING AT LINEBACKER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Another day, another linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   Strong-side linebacker Tony White, a two-year starter and one of
only three projected senior starters on defense, left practice
Monday morning with a strained back and is listed as day to day.
</P>
<P>
   A position that seemed the Bruins' deepest last spring is now
its thinnest. If the Bruins' season opener against No. 3-ranked
Alabama were today instead of Sept. 2, true freshman Brandon
Chillar would be starting at the strong-side spot.
</P>
<P>
   Billy Pieper, a versatile backup the last two seasons, retired
two months ago on the advice of doctors who said he was susceptible
to a serious spinal injury.
</P>
<P>
   Then Santi Hall and Asi Faoa were suspended Friday for the
season opener for disciplinary reasons. The following day, Hall
quit.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's four guys we thought we'd have and not one of them are
on the field right now,'' said defensive coordinator Bob Field.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report II: It looks as if guard Oscar Cabrera, who
sprained his right ankle Saturday, might not be ready for Alabama.
Senior Micah Webb has been shifted from backup right tackle and
will compete with redshirt freshman Shane Lehman to replace
Cabrera, who was on crutches Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
