u e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE16     08-15 0529
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    GRAPEVINE: News, notes from the wrestling industry
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WCW and Vince Russo are going to fire Goldberg. Not likely.
Despite the scenario played out at the ``New Blood Rising''
pay-per-view, Goldberg is not going anywhere and Russo is not going
to fire him. Expect this to become the WWF's long-running Vince
McMahon-Steve Austin feud come to life in the WCW.
</P>
<P>
   And who says Vince Russo lacks any original thoughts?
</P>
<P>
   In case the WCW doesn't get it, the wrestling fans do. For
example, at the pay-per-view, announcer Michael Buffer proclaimed
Booker T ``the people's champion.'' What did the crowd do, they
chanted ``Rocky, Rocky'' for the whole match awaiting the WWF's
people's champion, The Rock.
</P>
<P>
   Now if Vince only had some 20-something kids he could get to
help him ...
</P>
<P>
   _ With Vince McMahon's return to ``Raw'' expect to see a battle
for power in the WWF between McMahon and commissioner Mick Foley in
the fall. Foley still holds WWF crowds and his antics have been
some of the most popular in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jerry ``The King'' Lawler returned to the ring last week.
Lawler has been making appearances in the ring for the WWF minor
league organization in his hometown of Memphis. Lawler will battle
Tazz at ``SummerSlam.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Which bring us to a possible WCW or should I say NWA rip-off.
WCW commentator Mark Madden says he thinks the feud between Tazz
and Lawler is a tribute to former Georgia Championship Wrestling
announcer Gordon Solie, who spent years working with a heel
broadcast partner _ Roddy Piper. Eventually, Piper punched out Don
Moraco in defense of Solie.
</P>
<P>
   _ Speaking of ``SummerSlam,'' here's the most recent set of
matches. The Rock vs. Triple H vs. Kurt Angle for the heavyweight
championship; Chris Benoit vs. Chris Jericho; Undertaker vs. Kane;
Edge &AMP; Christian vs. The Hardy Boyz vs. the Dudley Boyz for the tag
team title and Val Venis vs. Eddie Guerrero for the
Intercontinental Championship.
</P>
<P>
   _ Also Steven Regal will return to the WWF for the Aug. 28 ``Raw
is War.'' Regal has been working in Memphis for the WWF. He is
trying to return from a series on injuries that has kept him on the
shelf for almost a year.
</P>
<P>
   _ Now Napster is going to have problems. The WWF's next CD _
``WWF The Music Volume 5'' _ is available for a free download on
the Internet's embattled free music site. And Napster thought
Metallica was angry.
</P>
<P>
   _ On ``Smackdown'' the WWF hyped the movie ``Highlander: End
Game.'' It will open in theaters on Sept. 1 and the WWF's Edge
appears in a few scenes.
</P>
<P>
   _ According to WWF announcer Jim Ross' weekly report, ``Stone
Cold'' Steve Austin met with his neurosurgeon last Thursday for an
examination of his surgically repaired spine. Dr. Lloyd Youngblood
feels that Austin could possibly return to action as early as
October. Austin will have another exam in six weeks. Of course with
the time off, Austin met with an orthopedic physician in San
Antonio about his knees and whether he is wearing the proper braces
to heal.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-15-00 1020EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
