<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, August 16, 2000 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ The number of times my wife and I turn to
each other to ask, ``What did he say?'' during the viewing of a TV
program or movie is increasing with alarming speed. Likely, it is
the onset of age and all the declines that brings with it but I
reserve much of the blame for mumbling actors and actresses and,
particularly, the British. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service.) MOVED
MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Kristofor, my son and only
child, insists that his frequent phone calls home are nothing less
than an adventure into never-never land where he often hesitates to
ask me what I'm up to fearing that I'll answer him truthfully. He
does assure me, however, that my ``differences'' are entertaining.
Naturally, I know of no differences, and I tell him so. Unless, of
course, this morning counts. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ Two recent cases from Texas show the state isn't
really interested in justice for all. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ Joe Murray's column will resume shortly.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
