accidents. By Christopher Drew.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-CONCORDE (London) _ British Airways plc grounded its
fleet of Concorde supersonic airliners Tuesday, after investigators
said they would urge the withdrawal of the airplane's airworthiness
certification following the fatal Concorde crash near Paris last
month. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   (An early version of this story will move by 3 p.m. EDT.)
</P>
<P>
   KOREA-REUNIONS (Seoul, South Korea) _ Two-hundred Korean
families separated for 50 years were reunited in Seoul and
Pyongyang Tuesday as North Korean security agents watched
carefully. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
   (An early version of this story will move by 3 p.m. EDT.)
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-MIDEAST (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ The Indonesian
president, Abdurrahman Wahid, has offered his help to solve
problems in the Middle East and will meet Tuesday with Israeli
representative Shimon Peres and with the Palestinian leader, Yasser
Arafat, on Wednesday. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-KASHMIR (Srinagar) _ On India's independence day, people
in Kashmir were too scared to go out. By Barry Bearak.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-BRIEFS (Undated) _ World news in brief.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; UNITED STATES &LR;  _ General
</P>
