first Jewish candidate named to a major party's national ticket, is
evident among Muslims and Arab-Americans. The sticking point:
concern about his fairness on Middle East issues. About 1,000
</P>
<P>
   CONVENTION-PAYOFF _ Political conventions, it turns out, aren't
the kind of big cash cows that civic boosters are fond of touting.
About 800
</P>
<P>
   LIEBERMAN-BLACKS _ The choice of a Jewish running mate with a
more conservative record on affirmative action may undermine the
Democratic ticket's ability to get the maximum return from its core
constituency. About 1,200
</P>
<P>
   ENTERGY-LEONARD _ An energetic combination of stand-up comedian
and accounting professor, Entergy chief executive J. Wayne Leonard
is sparking a change in corporate values on his way to the top of
the nation's largest power company. Photos. About 1,500
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-15-00 1305EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
