   XO-SAUCE-SOLVED (Undated) _ Dining out has its pleasure and its
mysteries. XO sauce is both. I recently developed an infatuation
with it. The flavor was intriguing: salty and sweet, hot and sour.
In it I could see tiny bits of dried shrimp, garlic, chilies and
scallop. There were very thin chopped-up noodles, too, and nearly
microscopic chips and flecks of unknown ingredients. If this was
XO, I had to get to the bottom of it. A critic's notebook by
William Grimes.
