technology heavyweights to throw his support behind the small but
growing Linux platform at the conference. By Alex Pham. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   CELERA-PROTEOMICS (Boston) _ Having unraveled the human genome
in June, Craig Venter of Celera Genomic is turning his attention to
proteomics _ the identifcation of proteins in cells _ although he
is hampered by computers that are simply too slow. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
