<P>
   COKE-EXEC _ Coca-Cola is expected to announce the hiring of a
new advertising director. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitute's
still a big fan of Windows and Microsoft. But in a clear sign that
alternative computer operating system Linux is catching on among
the heavyweights of computing, Dell is expected to announce Tuesday
new ways his company will support the growth of Linux. Other
companies - IBM, Hewlett-Packard and Compaq, to name a few - also
are planning new software and equipment based on Linux. (Keefe,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
