<P>
   RUSSIA-SUBMARINE (Moscow) _ Buffeted by storms, Russian rescuers
battled for a second day to reach 116 sailors trapped in a crippled
nuclear submarine on the sea floor, repeatedly trying to lower an
escape capsule to the stricken vessel. Efforts to rescue the Kursk,
lying motionless below the surface of the Barents Sea, were
hampered most of Tuesday by high winds and strong currents. There
had been no communication with the submarine since it went down,
and conditions inside were not known. It wasn't clear how much air
the crew had left and water appeared to be leaking in, officials
said. (Summary from wires) By Sabrina Tavernise and Christopher
Drew.
