<P>
   NJ-ABORTION (Trenton) _ Continuing a long line of decisions
interpreting its state constitution expansively, the New Jersey
Supreme Court on Tuesday struck down a law requiring that a parent
be notified before an unmarried girl under age 18 can get an
abortion. The court's 4-2 decision held that the notice requirement
denied minors seeking abortions the privacy rights accorded those
who continue their pregnancies.
