 PERSONALS: Meeting the Demands of the Public 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news
file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; Ivana Trump &LR;  told Marie Claire magazine that although she has
considered changing her trademark hairdo _ pinned to the top of her
head with yellow curls carefully cascading _ the public, her
public, absolutely refuses to allow it.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a curse,'' she said, with what the magazine described as
a sigh. ``When people see me without my hair up, (they) go
ballistic. Like I'm a different person and it's not what they
expected. They always want the hair.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Actor  &UR; Philip Seymour Hoffman &LR;  is at the Democratic convention
this week, getting ready to narrate a documentary directed by
 &UR; Donovan Leitch &LR;  about the presidential campaign. Hoffman is so
serious about playing the role of a journalist researching an
assignment, reports MSNBC, that when a fan greeted him he barked,
``Not now! I'm working.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Iman &LR; , 45, and  &UR; David Bowie &LR; , 53, had their first child,
daughter Alexandria Zahra Jones, on Aug. 15 in Los Angeles. And
 &UR; Bob Lacey &LR;  says the AOL headline ``Madonna Gives Birth to Boy''
would have been perfect for the Bethlehem Star.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``How is (Jesse Ventura) as a political leader? I have no idea &LR; 
 &UR; because I don't live in Minnesota and I don't know what he does. &LR; 
 &UR; But I don't buy into the fact that he's a joke just because he &LR; 
 &UR; was a wrestler. Mary Bono is there because her husband skied &LR; 
 &UR; into a tree. There's no such thing as qualifications in politics &LR; 
 &UR; anymore. Whoever can get there gets there, and then we'll see &LR; 
 &UR; what they can do.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Bill Maher &LR; , host of ``Politically Incorrect,'' in the
Washington newspaper the Hill.
</P>
