<HEADLINE>
FEINSTEIN SAYS CALIFORNIA KEY FOR GORE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICK ORLOV 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Worried that Democrats could be taking California
for granted, Sen. Dianne Feinstein on Tuesday said Vice President
Al Gore could lose the state without an all-out effort.
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course &UR; , &LR;  he could lose,'' Feinstein said at a breakfast
with California political reporters. ``This state has become used
to the attention given it by Bill Clinton and it will want to see
the same from Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
